a mobile terminal device that: suppresses the generation of echoes and howling that cause a deterioration in call quality; and achieves good call performance. The mobile terminal device (<b>100</b>) comprises a rear surface casing (<b>120</b>) and a battery cover (<b>130</b>) that covers the entire rear surface of the rear surface casing (<b>120</b>). Sound holes (<b>125</b>) for a microphone (<b>170</b>) and speaker sound holes (<b>124</b>) for a speaker (<b>150</b>) are arranged on the same rear surface of the rear surface casing (<b>120</b>). The rear surface casing (<b>120</b>) comprises a concave groove section (<b>129</b>), at least on the speaker (<b>150</b>) side and around the sound holes (<b>125</b>) for the microphone (<b>170</b>). The battery cover (<b>130</b>) comprises a convex protruding section (<b>139</b>) that fits into the groove section (<b>129</b>).</p></abstract></us-patent-application>